        "goal_understanding": "The goal of the game is to navigate a grid-based puzzle and complete all levels by stepping onto goal cells with a piece that matches the goal's required shape, color, and rotation simultaneously. Each level contains one or more goals, and all must be completed to advance. The ultimate objective is to finish all levels without losing all lives.",
        "mechanics_understanding": "The game uses a turn-based movement system where each move costs 1 stamina. Stamina is limited and when it reaches 0, a life is lost and stamina resets to its maximum. Running out of lives ends the game. Walls block movement, and the state always provides 'blocked_directions' to indicate impassable tiles. Modifier tiles change the carried piece's attributes: shape modifier cycles through 6 shapes, color modifier cycles through 4 colors (orange, blue, green, red), and rotation modifier rotates the piece 90\u00b0 clockwise through 4 directions. A goal cell only activates when the piece's shape, color, and rotation exactly match its requirements; stepping onto an activated goal completes it. Efficient route planning is essential to conserve stamina and avoid unnecessary backtracking, as seen in the episode where alternating between north and south moves wasted turns."
